During a meeting with top bankers, President Trump discussed the impact of the coronavirus outbreak on the economy and potential measures to support businesses and individuals. The CEOs of major banks reassured the President that the financial system is strong and well-capitalized. They also emphasized their commitment to providing credit and relief to customers affected by the virus. The bankers expressed support for fiscal stimulus to help small businesses and individuals, with suggestions such as adjusting or eliminating the payroll tax. The President announced that he would be making a statement later that evening to address the situation.